result.execSummary:
Lucas C Stonecipher III was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Lucas C Stonecipher III was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Def appears in custody & w/Atty Alyssa Armbrust.  Atty Mark D. Bensen for State. Copy of Governor's warrant filed; Oklahoma has been advised and DA expects def will be transported within 3-5 days.

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Alyssa Armbrust.  Atty Mark D. Bensen for State. Atty Bensen states he was advised that there was a problem with paperwork and the governor's warrant is expected to be received either today or early next week. State requests adj.  Hearing scheduled for September 24, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Alyssa Armbrust.  Atty Sandra Jo Giernoth for State. Complaint served on defendant. Def previously made initial appearance and court extended bail. State still waiting on Oklahoma warrant.  Hearing scheduled for September 18, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Alyssa Armbrust.  Atty Peter John Cannon for State. State indicates state of Oklahoma is pursuing governor's warrant and anticipate 4 month delay in getting that. State to follow up regarding status and time limits. Court extends def's bail and recommits def up to another 60 days.  Hearing scheduled for August 20, 2015 at 01:15 pm.

Def appears in custody & w/Atty  State Public Defenders Office.  Atty Peter John Cannon for State.  Def given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found. Def admits he is the subject named on the complaint. Def not willing to waive extradition at this time. State to pursue governor's warrant.  Hearing scheduled for July 22, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
Extradition - Fugitive from State of Oklahoma, to-wit:  County of Payne, for six counts of second degree forgery and five counts of false pawn declaration
